#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:6
msgid ""
"Generally you use UNIX signals to manage the master, but we are running "
"out of signal numbers and (more importantly) not needing to mess with "
"PIDs greatly simplifies the implementation of external management "
"scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:9
msgid ""
"So, instead of signals, you can tell the master to create a UNIX named "
"pipe (FIFO) that you may use to issue commands to the master."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:11
msgid ""
"To create a FIFO just add ``--master-fifo <filename>`` then start issuing"
" commands to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:17
msgid "You can send multiple commands in one shot."
msgstr ""

