msgid "FIFO slots"
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:51
msgid ""
"uWSGI supports up to 10 different FIFO files. By default the first "
"specified is bound (mapped as '0')."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:53
msgid ""
"During the instance's lifetime you can change from one FIFO to another by"
" simply sending the number of the FIFO slot to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:64
msgid "By default ``/tmp/fifo0`` will be allocated, but after sending:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:70
msgid "the ``/tmp/fifo1`` file will be bound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:72
msgid ""
"This is very useful to map FIFO files to specific instance when you "
"(ab)use the 'fork the master' command (the 'f' one)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:78
msgid ""
"After sending this command, a new uWSGI instance (inheriting all of the "
"bound sockets) will be spawned, the old one will be put in \"paused\" "
"mode (the 'p' command)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../MasterFIFO.rst:80
msgid ""
"As we have sent the '1' command before 'f' and 'p' the old instance will "
"now accept commands on /tmp/fifo1 (the slot 1), and the new one will use "
"the default one ('0')."
msgstr ""

